Travel Through Time Camporee hosted by Community 6

Come Travel Through Time with the Waterâ€™s Edge Girl Scouts.  Experience different cultures for long ago, around the world.  You can build a medieval catapult, experience arts from Colonial America, learn traditional dances from the Marantha Empire in India, and much more.

* This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts of Gateway Council, and registered & approved adult volunteers.

* For safety and supervision reasons, troops and individuals are not permitted to bring non-Girl Scouts or siblings.

* Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the camporee.

$30/girl, $30/adult
